<% content_for :title do %>Automations & bots | <%= installation_brand_name %> User Guide<% end %>
<% content_for :meta_description do %>Automations, webhook agent bots, and API channel in <%= installation_brand_name %> for event-driven support workflows.<% end %>

<h1>Automations & bots</h1>
<p class="lead">
  <strong>Automations</strong> run rules when events occur inside <%= installation_brand_name %>.
  <strong>Agent bots</strong> send conversation events to your external server.
  The <strong>API channel</strong> integrates custom messaging backends.
</p>

<h2>Automations</h2>
<h3>Events (examples)</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Conversation created</li>
  <li>Message created</li>
  <li>Conversation updated (status, assignee)</li>
  <li>Conversation opened / resolved</li>
</ul>
<h3>Conditions</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Inbox equals …</li>
  <li>Message content contains …</li>
  <li>Assignee is …</li>
  <li>Custom attribute values</li>
</ul>
<h3>Actions</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Assign agent or team</li>
  <li>Add label</li>
  <li>Send email to team</li>
  <li>Send message (customer or private note)</li>
  <li>Send webhook event</li>
  <li>Send attachment</li>
  <li>Mute / resolve conversation</li>
</ul>
<h3>Create automation</h3>
<ol>
  <li><strong>Settings → Automation → Add automation</strong></li>
  <li>Name and select event</li>
  <li>Add conditions (AND logic)</li>
  <li>Add one or more actions</li>
  <li>Activate and test with a sample conversation</li>
</ol>

<h2>Agent bots (webhook)</h2>
<p>Unlike Captain AI, agent bots POST JSON to <strong>your URL</strong> for custom logic (Dialogflow, Rasa, internal CRM, etc.).</p>
<ol>
  <li><strong>Settings → Bots → Add bot</strong></li>
  <li>Name and <strong>Outgoing URL</strong> (HTTPS endpoint)</li>
  <li>Optional: access token for authentication</li>
  <li>Attach bot to inbox: <strong>Inbox → Configuration → Bot</strong></li>
</ol>
<h3>Bot events sent to your server</h3>
<ul>
  <li><code>message_created</code> — new customer or agent message</li>
  <li><code>widget_triggered</code> — visitor opened chat</li>
  <li>Other events per API documentation</li>
</ul>
<p>Your server responds with messages to send back to the customer via API.</p>

<h2>API channel</h2>
<p>For fully custom channels (mobile app chat, proprietary messenger):</p>
<ol>
  <li><strong>Add inbox → API</strong></li>
  <li>Use inbox identifier and agent API tokens</li>
  <li>Create/update contacts and conversations via REST API</li>
  <li>Receive webhooks for agent replies to your system</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Email continuity:</strong> When a contact in an API inbox has an email address, agent replies can also be sent by email so users can continue the thread outside your app. Ensure contacts include valid email addresses.</p>
<p>See developer API docs on your installation for endpoint details.</p>

<h2>Captain vs automation vs bot</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Captain</strong> — built-in AI, documents, Copilot — <a href="<%= guide_page_path('captain') %>">Captain guide</a></li>
  <li><strong>Automation</strong> — if-this-then-that inside <%= installation_brand_name %></li>
  <li><strong>Agent bot</strong> — your code handles intelligence via webhook</li>
</ul>

<h2>Best practices</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Start with one simple automation (e.g. label “spam” on keyword)</li>
  <li>Log webhook bot responses for debugging</li>
  <li>Hand off to human when bot confidence is low</li>
  <li>Test automations in a test inbox before production</li>
</ul>

